Application of AI for improving match quota for
seagoing personnel in the Maritime Industry
Objective
Develop an AI that beats the manual/current matching quota: it finds the best candidate(s) /
match(es) for an open vacancy in a minimum amount of time.
Use case
Matching of seafarer profiles and company vacancies
What is the probability that profile X is accepted for job posting Y?
What factors and factor combination in profile and vacancy are mainly influencing the
probability of a successful match (defined as signing of employment contract)?
What can seafarers and/or companies do/change to increase the probability of a successful
match?
Project Deliverables
Define & propose data structure and data point enhancement as basis for AI use case
a.
Data analysis: what data is missing to improve the AI
b.
How to structure existing & future data to maximize usability for AI
c.
How to train the AI
Propose generic AI architecture
Implement generic AI architecture
Define roadmap incl. targets on AI case usage
About TURTLE
The bloodstream of the global economy, ocean shipping, is run by nearly 2 million seafarers globally.
However, the labor market for seafarers is fragmented, in-transparent and struggles with corruption.
TURTLE wants to empower the seafarer and enable a digital, efficient, and compliant market free from
corruption and other illegal and immoral activities.
As a team of industry professionals, we are building a global online job marketplace that connects
ship owners and seafarers directly. Since the launch in February 2021 more than 21.000 seafarers
registered and several of the market leading shipping companies are working with TURTLE.
